[SN]TITLE[SN]
Police inspector Zoe Hallam rowed dinghy despite 'bad back'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A police inspector who lied about the severity of her back injuries after a car crash has been sacked after she was covertly filmed rowing a dinghy.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Zoe Hallam was surveilled while she was on holiday after her Nottinghamshire Police colleagues became suspicious.
She and her husband, also a police inspector, were arrested but the force said he was "completely exonerated".
Mrs Hallam, 48, was dismissed after gross misconduct between December 2011 and November 2013 was proven.
She was said to have exaggerated the severity of her injuries in order to get medical retirement and receive an enhanced pension.
